# Hub auto-connect

When **HUB_SSH_*** secrets exist, the agent connects to the owner hub **automatically** — do not ask the owner to say "connect to hub" first.

## When to connect

Run **before** any hub-side work (WSL install, `adb`, bubble phone hub, desktop helper, repo on laptop):

```bash
python3 -m shorts_bot.hub_remote ensure --quiet
```

Or run a remote command (connects first if needed):

```bash
python3 -m shorts_bot.hub_remote run -- python3 --version
bash scripts/hub_run.sh cd ~/proof-codex-ai && git pull
python3 -m shorts_bot.desktop_hub.cli ping   # needs Windows helper running
python3 -m shorts_bot.hub_control.cli status
```

## Bootstrap

`bash scripts/install.sh` already calls `hub_connect.sh --quiet` when hub secrets are present.

## Status / verify

```bash
python3 -m shorts_bot.hub_remote status
python3 -m shorts_bot.hub_remote verify   # full SSH smoke test
```

## If connect fails

Hub laptop asleep, WSL closed, or Tailscale down on HP — tell owner **one step**: open Ubuntu on HP and run `sudo tailscale up`. Do not blame secret setup unless `status` shows `secrets_configured: False`.

